  <div id="troubleshoot1" class="troubleshoot">
    <h3>Troubleshooting Tips for Toggle Switch (Closed)</h3>
    <p>If the measured voltage is not as expected (e.g., 24V), check for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Power supply issues or incorrect voltage.</li>
      <li>Faulty switch contacts.</li>
      <li>Loose connections or damaged wires.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Note:</strong> Ensure the switch is in the closed (On) position when measuring voltage.</p>
  </div>

  <div id="troubleshoot2" class="troubleshoot">
    <h3>Troubleshooting Tips for Toggle Switch (Open)</h3>
    <p>If the measured value is not OL (Open Line), check for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Short circuits in the wiring.</li>
      <li>Stuck or faulty switch contacts.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Note:</strong> Ensure the switch is in the open (Off) position before measuring resistance.</p>
  </div>

  <div id="troubleshoot3" class="troubleshoot">
    <h3>Troubleshooting Tips for Push Button Switch (Closed)</h3>
    <p>If the measured voltage is not as expected (e.g., 24V), check for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Power supply issues or incorrect voltage.</li>
      <li>Faulty push button contacts.</li>
      <li>Loose connections or damaged wires.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Note:</strong> Ensure the push button is in the pressed position when measuring voltage.</p>
  </div>

  <div id="troubleshoot4" class="troubleshoot">
    <h3>Troubleshooting Tips for Push Button Switch (Open)</h3>
    <p>If the measured value is not OL (Open Line), check for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Short circuits in the wiring.</li>
      <li>Stuck or faulty push button contacts.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Note:</strong> Ensure the push button is in the released position before measuring resistance.</p>
  </div>
